

#1 issue - OWASP 2023.  #4 Unrestricted resource consumption.

We currently do not have ANY restrictions to how often a user can use our service,
Which can be expensive if a malicious actor sets up an automated means to call our service.
This could be very expensive as we pay for OpenAI,  but it could also be similar to DDOS as our service is limited by the rate in GeoApify

How to solve?
Rate limits and Caching the results from our external APIs, This causes frequently searched locations to only needing to call the APIs when the cache becomes stale.


#2 issue - OWASP 2023 #10 Unsafe Consumption of APIs
While we validate some responses like that from the OpenAI,
we should also validate the responses from OpenGeofy and OpenMeteo.

The actual security risk from this is low due to how we use the responses but the implementation is still relevant to show
how we avoid passing malformed data down the chain.


#3 issue - OWASP 2023 #8 Security Missconfiguration (More like no configuration)

A low risk issue at the moment.  However without a cors config a potential frontend script cannot call on our API.
As I have modeled my API akin to other publicly available APIs like SWAPI,
And also do not have debugging endpoints like that of actuator.
I fail to see how a cors policy could become "To Permissive" in the projects current state.

BUT! this would no longer be true if the project expands and includes more protected endpoints.